# Granot Extension Architecture

- This WXT extension supports Chrome and Firefox. Keep browser APIs behind `webextension-polyfill`/WXT globals so `pnpm build` and `pnpm build:firefox` keep working.
- `src/config.ts` owns CRM URL patterns, `VANTAGE_API_BASE`, and bundled `VITE_VANTAGE_API_SECRET`. The secret is sent as `x-api-secret` to protected Vantage `/api/v1` routes.
- `src/entrypoints/granot-crm.content.ts` is the page reader. It must read the current Granot DOM on demand and return structured data to the popup; avoid mutating or adding controls to the Granot CRM page.
- Only parse the visible `Follow Up Estimates` section. Do not sync `Booked Jobs` rows, and do not use CSV links unless a future task explicitly changes the source of truth.
- Granot table `ref_no` contains the Mongo `_id` for the Vantage `FormLead`. Granot `prior` is the source for Vantage `quoted`.
- Treat only exact `prior` values `0` and `1` as syncable: `0 -> quoted=false`, `1 -> quoted=true`. Show other values as unsupported and skip them by default.
- `src/entrypoints/popup/` owns the user workflow: scan, preview parsed rows, select/deselect rows, sync selected rows, and sync all supported rows.
- Sync selected rows by preflighting `GET /api/v1/form-leads/:id`, comparing current `quoted`, and PATCHing only when the value changes. PATCHing triggers the server's WaitUntil Google Sheet sync.
- Report row-level outcomes in the popup: updated, unchanged, skipped/unsupported, invalid `ref_no`, not found, and failed.
- Before shipping extension changes, run `pnpm compile`, `pnpm build`, and `pnpm build:firefox`.
